criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        - Mild to moderate lower face and/or submental laxity that is amenable to improvement with
        non-invasive intervention and is not severe enough for surgical intervention;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Scarring in area(s) to be treated;

          -  Any active implants (e.g., pacemakers or defibrillators) in the area(s) to be treated;

          -  Any metallic implants in area(s) to be treated;

          -  Any open wounds or lesions in the area(s) to be treated;

          -  Body mass index (BMI) less than 19 or greater than 30; or

          -  Gain or loss of ≥ 2 BMI units within the previous 90 days or has the intention to gain
             or lose ≥ 2 BMI units during the course of the trial.
